abstract:
[{'text': 'The present disclosure relates HER2 antibodies and to the de novo design of structure-based design targeted antibodies. According to the current disclosure, computer-implemented methods of designing an antibody sequences that will bind the HER2 with significant affinity at a target receptor epitope are disclosed. The method utilizes artificial intelligence (Al) and machine learning (ML) models that are trained to predict improved biomolecule (e.g., antibody or antibody fragments) binding sequences or other desirable properties using known biomolecule/binding partner complexes. A designed HER2 antibody is generated by replacing matching residues with different residues such that a predicted affinity is increased.', 'language': 'en', 'truncated': False}
 {'text': 'The present disclosure relates HER2 antibodies and to the de novo design of structure-based design targeted antibodies. According to the current disclosure, computer-implemented methods of designing an antibody sequences that will bind the HER2 with significant affinity at a target receptor epitope are disclosed. The method utilizes artificial intelligence (Al) and machine learning (ML) models that are trained to predict improved biomolecule (e.g., antibody or antibody fragments) binding sequences or other desirable properties using known biomolecule/binding partner complexes. A designed HER2 antibody is generated by replacing matching residues with different residues such that a predicted affinity is increased.', 'language': 'en', 'truncated': False}
 {'text': 'La présente divulgation se rapporte à des anticorps anti-HER2 et à la conception de novo d&#39;anticorps ciblés à conception à base de structure. La présente divulgation divulgue des procédés mis en œuvre par ordinateur de conception d&#39;une séquence d&#39;anticorps qui se lient au HER2 avec une affinité significative au niveau d&#39;un épitope de récepteur cible. Le procédé utilise des modèles d&#39;intelligence artificielle (lA) et d&#39;apprentissage automatique (ML) qui sont entraînés pour prédire des séquences de liaison de biomolécule (par exemple, des fragments d&#39;anticorps ou des anticorps) améliorées ou d&#39;autres propriétés souhaitables à l&#39;aide de complexes de biomolécule/partenaire de liaison connus. Un anticorps anti-HER2 conçu est généré en remplaçant des résidus correspondants par des résidus différents de telle sorte qu&#39;une affinité prédite est accrue.', 'language': 'fr', 'truncated': False}
